  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by partially restituting the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the 10-year demand from the spectator is disproportionate to the scale of the crime and the defendant's character. Considering the mitigating factors of a clean record and partial repayment, a custodial sentence of 6 months is sufficient to address the criminality while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
